      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Way We Live Now Poll</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Barry Collodi letter praises May 7 special issue on what we think and how we feel at start of new millennium</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was overwhelmed by your special issue (May 7), with its remarkably positive, incisive look at what we think and how we feel at the start of the new millennium. We appear, on the whole, to retain belief in something bigger than ourselves.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>I was overwhelmed by your special issue (May 7), with its remarkably positive, incisive look at what we think and how we feel at the start of the new millennium. We appear, on the whole, to retain belief in something bigger than ourselves.</p>
        <p>Lorenzo Albacete's Lives column, ''Secrets of the Confessional,'' was particularly effective, with its understanding of our universal need to be truthful when it pains us most. And to find humor even then.</p>
        <p>Thank you for the reality check -- good medicine and a great deal to think about.</p>
        <p>Barry Collodi</p>
        <p>New York</p>
      </block>
